    {
      "id": "49c88bf6878b107c4684768501a8dae65f75dcea",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 251,
        "name": "Bob Glossman",
        "email": "bob.glossman@intel.com",
        "username": "bogl",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-22 14:45:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nwhile the way to check for rhel vs. other environments may be sloppy or bad, I don't think installing init scripts unconditionally is the right solution.  As far as I know the scripts don't work correctly everywhere, in particular in SLES environments.  Installing them unconditionally in all cases may have undesirable side effects.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "14abf2839e15f950e2d3117bd1c86f628b049a9b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2014-10-22 16:33:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.5/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/116b3dac-5a09-11e4-8dbb-5254006e85c2).  Ran 6 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a91860367f4ad418fdeca2a159cbe084eb86647a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 403,
        "name": "Autotest",
        "email": "autotest@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "autotest",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2014-10-22 17:07:03.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nShadow Autotest2 started enforced review-dne-part-2 session.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "12ed8804e3c7f5110a8f4d9160e6af8bf3b4ac5d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2014-10-22 17:47:03.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nYes, but having the scripts where they were not needed was much less of a problem then _not_ having them where they are needed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c7ed1e5152512105116b8b1247f5798bc7c98981",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 301,
        "name": "Dmitry Eremin",
        "email": "dmitry.eremin@intel.com",
        "username": "dmiter",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-22 18:27:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe scripts are not used by default. It's up to user use them or not. I would agree that having a side effects from them is not so big issue rather don't have them at all.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
